<html>
<body style="margin:5px 0px 0px 5px">
<div style="font-size:18pt; font-family:verdana; font-weight:bold">
    <%= @title %>
</div>
<hr style="border:solid 1px #000080" />
<div style="font-family:verdana; font-size:10pt;width:640px;">
Cannot access MySQL database. The error message is:
	<div style="background:#DDDDDD;margin:1em 0em 1em 0em;padding:1em 30px 1em 30px"><code><%= @errmsg.message %></code></div>
This is probably because the chart demonstration database has not been set up yet. To run this example, 
you need to:
<br /><br />
<ul>
	<li>Set up "config/database.yml" to use a MySQL database as the database for this
	application. (You may need to restart the application after this step.)<br /><br /></li>
	
	<li>Import the table and records in "db/sample.sql" into the database.</li>
</ul>

If you just want to view the sample code without setting up the database, 
<%= link_to "click here", :controller => "cddemo", :action => "viewsource", 
	:ctrl_file => @ctrl_file, :view_file => File.dirname(File.dirname(
	File.expand_path(__FILE__))) + "/#{@controller.controller_name}/index.rhtml" %>.
</ul>
</div>
</body>
</html>
